{"insight":"Some distance keeps the hand open","plainSummary":"A wise gap can keep truth from becoming something I claim, control, or own.","atAGlance":"Some distance is not coldness. It can keep my care from turning into control. When I close a gap too soon, insight can become possession. The question is what the space protects.","match":["protective distance"],"tags":["practice","humility","restraint","love"]}
